The Vice President visited the Willow Way Program Home in Billings, Montana to discuss the issue of drug abuse and addiction. He commended the efforts of local law enforcement and emphasized the importance of securing the southern border to prevent the flow of drugs into the country. The Vice President also reassured the people of Montana that the administration is committed to providing resources and support for organizations and individuals dealing with drug addiction. He mentioned the recent agreement with Mexico to address the drug crisis and highlighted the need for strong law enforcement and recovery programs. The Vice President and Senator Daines expressed hope for the future and discussed the importance of enforcement, education, and recovery efforts. They also addressed the funding for the HIDTA (High Intensity Drug Trafficking Areas) program and stated that they will work with Congress to ensure it has the necessary resources.